The names of the newly elected leadership of the African National Congress (ANC) in the Mopani Region were announced during its much awaited conference earlier today (Saturday). ANC Limpopo Media Liaison Officer Aluwani Netsianda said Pule Shayi was chosen as the new chairperson, taking over from Seaparo Sekoati, with Violet Mathye as his deputy. Basikopo Makamu was re-elected as Regional Secretary and Peter Matlou elected as his deputy. Gerson Molapisane is the new treasurer in the region. Story: Yolande Nel